At the bottom, there is an overlay with buttons for toggling the front/back camera, capturing a photo or video, and viewing the last captured media. media_viewer_interface:toolbar_options.effect: tap to navigate to the media_properties_dialog, which is a dialog showing the properties of the media. The dialog includes a title bar with the text 'Properties'. Below the title, there is a scrollable area containing various property details such as name, path, size, resolution, last modified date, date taken, camera, EXIF data, and GPS coordinates. At the bottom, there are two buttons: 'Remove EXIF' and 'OK'.

media_viewer_interface:properties_button.name: media_viewer_interface:properties_button
media_viewer_interface:properties_button.description: A button to view the properties of the media.
media_viewer_interface:properties_button.effect: tap to navigate to the media_properties_dialog, which is a dialog showing the properties of the media. The dialog includes a title bar with the text 'Properties'. Below the title, there is a scrollable area containing various property details such as name, path, size, resolution, last modified date, date taken, camera, EXIF data, and GPS coordinates. At the bottom, there are two buttons: 'Remove EXIF' and 'OK'.

media_viewer_interface:edit_button.description: A button to edit the media.
media_viewer_interface:edit_button.effect: tap to navigate to the edit_with_interface, which is a selection interface for choosing an application to edit media. It includes a title bar with the text 'Edit with'. Below the title, there is a list of available applications displayed in a ListView. Each application item includes an icon and a button with the application's name. At the bottom, there are two buttons: 'Just once' and 'Always'.

The dialog includes a message indicating the action, a checkbox for not asking again in this session, and two buttons: 'No' and 'Yes'.

<framelayout>
 <linearlayout>
  <framelayout resource_id="content">
   <viewgroup resource_id="options_content">
    <linearlayout resource_id="dynamic_content">
    </linearlayout>
    <framelayout resource_id="static_content">
     <button resource_id="destination_spinner">
      <linearlayout>
       <imageview resource_id="icon">
       </imageview>
       <relativelayout>
        <button resource_id="title">
        </button>
       </relativelayout>
      </linearlayout>
     </button>
    </framelayout>
    <button resource_id="summary_content">
     <button>
     </button>
     <button resource_id="copies_count_summary">
     </button>
     <button resource_id="paper_size_summary">
     </button>
    </button>
    <framelayout resource_id="embedded_content_container">
     <view resource_id="embedded_content_scrim">
     </view>
     <recyclerview resource_id="preview_content">
      <checkbox resource_id="preview_page">
       <view resource_id="page_content">
       </view>
       <relativelayout resource_id="page_footer">
        <checkbox resource_id="page_number">
        </checkbox>
        <imageview resource_id="page_selector">
        </imageview>
       </relativelayout>
      </checkbox>
     </recyclerview>
    </framelayout>
    <button resource_id="print_button">
    </button>
   </viewgroup>
  </framelayout>
 </linearlayout>
</framelayout>
